## 4. Component Architecture

### 4.1 Backend — FastAPI Application Server

**Entry point:** [backend/main.py](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/main.py)

```
FastAPI App (v2.0.0)
├── CORS Middleware     — permissive for Chrome extension compatibility
├── Lifespan Manager   — MCP client init on startup, graceful close on shutdown
├── /health            — liveness probe: returns MCP connection status
├── /                  — API metadata
└── Router (/api/*)    — all business endpoints (see §6)
```

**Key design decisions:**

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| `asynccontextmanager` lifespan | Replaces deprecated `startup`/`shutdown` events in FastAPI ≥0.93 |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*` default | Chrome extensions require permissive CORS; controlled via env var |
| `uvicorn[standard]` | Includes WebSocket and file-watch support for hot-reload in development |
| `python:3.11-slim` Docker base | Minimal footprint; 3.11 required for `tomllib` stdlib and performance gains |

---

### 4.2 AI Agent Layer — Google ADK

**Core module:** [backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py)

#### 4.2.1 Agent Configuration

```python
Agent(
    name="flowgent",
    model=get_agent_model(),       # runtime-configurable: Gemini / OpenRouter / Azure
    instruction=SYSTEM_INSTRUCTION, # ~4 KB detailed prompt
    tools=[11 async functions]
)
```

#### 4.2.2 Tool Inventory

| Category | Tool | Description |
|----------|------|-------------|
| **Research** | [get_workflow_recipe](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#132-158) | Pre-built workflow skeletons (schedule/loop/webhook patterns) |
| | [web_search](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#99-128) | DuckDuckGo search for API docs, webhook formats, best practices |
| | [search_workflow_templates](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#196-214) | n8n community template search by keyword |
| | [get_workflow_template](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#216-234) | Full template JSON retrieval by ID |
| | [search_nodes](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#160-175) | Node type discovery by name/description |
| | [get_node_documentation](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#177-194) | Full parameter/typeVersion docs for a node type |
| **Validation** | [validate_workflow_json](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#236-254) | Pre-create structural validation via MCP |
| **Management** | [list_workflows](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#258-283) | List workflows from connected n8n |
| | [get_workflow](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/api/routes.py#121-157) | Retrieve workflow by ID |
| | [create_workflow](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#323-391) | Create new workflow with nodes + connections |
| | [update_workflow](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/api/routes.py#190-231) | Partial update of an existing workflow |
| | [execute_workflow](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#420-450) | Trigger workflow execution |

#### 4.2.3 Multi-Provider LLM Support

The agent uses **LiteLLM** as a provider-agnostic adapter:

```
LLM_MODEL=litellm/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-chat  → OpenRouter (default, free tier)
LLM_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash                            → Google Gemini
LLM_MODEL=azure/gpt-5.2                               → Azure OpenAI
LLM_MODEL=litellm/openrouter/moonshot/kimi-k2-thinking → Kimi K2 Thinking (reasoning model)
```

Provider selection happens at import time (`agent/config.py`). API keys for each provider are injected into `os.environ` before ADK initializes its internal client.

#### 4.2.4 Session Management

Sessions are stored in an `InMemorySessionService` (ADK-provided). Each HTTP request carries an optional `session_id` in the chat message context, defaulting to `"default_session"`. Sessions persist for the lifetime of the process (no disk persistence by design — stateless deployment target).

#### 4.2.5 Reasoning Model Post-Processing

When `kimi-k2-thinking` or similar chain-of-thought models are active, the [_strip_reasoning()](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#46-95) function post-processes responses to remove internal thought blocks before returning text to the user.

