## 6. API Contract

**Base URL:** `http://localhost:8000` (configurable)  
**Auth:** Credentials passed per-request via JSON body (`n8n_config`) or custom headers for workflow/execution endpoints.

### Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `GET` | `/health` | Liveness check + MCP connection status |
| `GET` | `/` | API metadata |
| `POST` | `/api/chat` | Chat with the AI agent |
| `GET` | `/api/workflows` | List all n8n workflows |
| `GET` | `/api/workflows/{id}` | Get single workflow with full node/connection data |
| `POST` | `/api/workflows` | Create a new workflow |
| `PUT` | `/api/workflows/{id}` | Partial update of an existing workflow |
| `POST` | `/api/execute` | Execute a workflow with optional input data |
| `GET` | `/api/node-info/{type:path}` | Retrieve node documentation (cached) |
| `GET` | `/api/executions` | Get execution history, optional `?workflow_id=` filter |

### Key Request/Response Schemas

**POST /api/chat**
```json
{
  "message": "Create a workflow that sends Slack alerts for new GitHub stars",
  "n8n_config": { "instance_url": "https://my.n8n.cloud", "api_key": "n8n_..." },
  "context": { "session_id": "user-abc-123" }
}
```
```json
{
  "response": "I created the workflow '...' (ID: 42). It uses...",
  "workflow_data": null,
  "action": null
}
```

**Custom Headers (workflow/execution endpoints)**
```
X-N8N-Instance-URL: https://my.n8n.cloud
X-N8N-API-Key: n8n_...
```

