## 7. Security Architecture

### 7.1 Credential Handling

| Location | Storage | Risk |
|----------|---------|------|
| Chrome Extension | `chrome.storage.local` (encrypted by Chrome) | Low — sandboxed per extension |
| API Requests | In-memory only, per-request context | Low — never persisted to disk |
| Environment ([backend/.env](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/.env)) | File on disk / container env vars | Medium — standard secret management required |

### 7.2 Known Limitations

> [!WARNING]
> The `agent/context.py` module stores n8n credentials in a **module-level global variable**, not in a request-scoped or thread-local store. Under concurrent request load, credentials from one request could leak into another. This is safe in the current single-threaded async I/O model but must be addressed before multi-worker deployment.

**Mitigation path:** Replace the global with a `contextvars.ContextVar` for proper async request isolation.

### 7.3 CORS Policy

The backend defaults to `ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*` (required for Chrome extension compatibility), configurable via environment variable for production lockdown.

### 7.4 Input Validation

All incoming request bodies are validated by **Pydantic v2** before reaching business logic. JSON payloads passed to [create_workflow](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/agent/flowgent_agent.py#323-391) / [update_workflow](file:///d:/flowgent/backend/api/routes.py#190-231) are parsed and re-serialized, preventing injection of malformed structures into the n8n API.

