## 8. Deployment & Infrastructure

### 8.1 Local Development

```
Backend:  uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
Extension: Chrome → Load Unpacked → extension/
n8n:      Docker or n8n.cloud (configured via settings panel)
```

### 8.2 Cloud Deployment (Google Cloud Run)

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim
WORKDIR /app
RUN apt-get install -y gcc
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt   # layer-cached
COPY . .
ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 PORT=8080
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["sh", "-c", "uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT"]
```

Cloud Run receives `PORT` as an environment variable and the container honours it. The deployment is fully stateless — any restart or scale-out event produces a fresh process with empty session memory.

### 8.3 Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| `LLM_MODEL` | Yes | LiteLLM model string (e.g. `litellm/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-chat`) |
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | If OpenRouter | API key from openrouter.ai |
| `GOOGLE_GENAI_API_KEY` | If Gemini | Key from Google AI Studio |
| `AZURE_AI_API_KEY` / `AZURE_API_BASE` | If Azure | Azure AI endpoint credentials |
| `FALLBACK_LLM_MODEL` | Optional | Secondary model on rate limit |
| `N8N_MCP_URL` | Yes | MCP server endpoint |
| `N8N_MCP_API_KEY` | Yes | MCP server API key |
| `PORT` / `HOST` | Optional | Server bind config (default: 8000 / 0.0.0.0) |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | Optional | CORS origins (default: `*`) |

